item.title: CVE-2022-34405|2024-08-03T09:07:16.290Z -- dell -- cpg%20drivers
item.description: An improper access control vulnerability was identified in the Realtek audio driver. A local authenticated malicious user may potentially exploit this vulnerability by waiting for an administrator to launch the application and attach to the process to elevate privileges on the system.
